Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Halve and peel the @red onion{1}, then chop each half into quarters. Halve the @apple{1}, remove the core and chop each half into three wedges (no need to peel).

Trim the @carrot{3}, then halve lengthways (no need to peel). Chop into roughly 1cm wide, 5cm long batons. Chop the @potatoes{450}(chopped into 2cm chunks, no need to peel).

Pick the @sage{½} leaves from their stalks and roughly chop (discard the stalks).

Pop the potatoes onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{for roasting}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat.

Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{30-40%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, pop the onion, apple, carrot and sage onto another large baking tray and drizzle with oil. Season with salt and pepper, toss to coat, then spread out in a single layer.

Place the @British honey mustard sausages{8} on top of the veg, then roast on the middle shelf of your oven until the veg is tender and the sausages are cooked through, ~{25-30%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. The sausages are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

== Buttery Sauce ==

About 5 mins before the sausages and veg are cooked, pop a small #saucepan{} on medium heat.

Add the @onion marmalade{40%g}, @chicken stock paste{10%g} and @water{50%ml} to the pan. Stir together and bring to the boil, then remove from the heat and stir in the @butter{20%g} until melted.

Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed, then set aside.

== Assembly ==

When everything's cooked, add the roast potatoes to the veg tray. Stir everything together.

Reheat the buttery sauce if necessary.

Share the roasted veg and sausages between your plates, then spoon over the buttery sauce to finish. Enjoy!